value.title: Senior adviser: Biden to be tested again Sunday

value.title: Dr. Sanjay Gupta: Trump shouldn't be discharged tomorrow

value.title: Advisers made last-minute push to get reluctant Trump to Walter Reed

value.title: Trump's campaign rocked by coronavirus one month before election

value.title: 'This was avoidable': Trump has been downplaying the virus from the start

value.title: Mike Pence and his wife tested negative Friday morning.
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence announced Friday that he and his wife, Karen, had tested negative for the coronavirus, just hours after President Trump and the first lady announced they had both tested positive and were quarantining at the White House.

value.title: Trump says he'll overturn 'ridiculous' gender-neutral Navy terms

value.title: Trump set to defy task force recommendations with Wisconsin rallies
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump is expected to again defy recommendations from his own administration's coronavirus task force and guidance from local officials Saturday, traveling to Wisconsin for campaign rallies at airplane hangars in La Crosse and Green Bay.

value.title: Former commander of US forces in Afghanistan endorses Biden
value.excerpt: It's striking how many retired military leaders, many of whom have been apolitical for decades, have stepped up to denounce Trump, endorse Biden, or both.

value.title: Three-quarters of LGBTQ voters back Joe Biden, GLAAD poll finds
value.excerpt: With the presidential election just a month away, 75 percent of LGBTQ voters said they support Biden, while 17 percent back Trump, according to a GLAAD poll.

value.title: Trump signs spending bill to keep government open until December 11
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump early Thursday morning signed a spending bill to keep the government open until December 11, according to a tweet from White House spokesman Judd Deere.

value.title: Federal judge refuses to stop mail-in voting in Montana, blasts Trump-backed 'fiction' of massive voter fraud

value.title: Joe Biden and Kamala Harris don't want to talk about changes to the Supreme Court

value.title: Biden: 'He's the racist'

value.title: Biden paid nearly $300,000 in federal income taxes in 2019

value.title: Trump's Supreme Court pick on Capitol Hill for meeting with GOP senators

value.title: Trump announces plan to deploy 150 million Covid rapid tests previously touted
